h <i>scēap</i> ‘sheep’), + Old English <i>wīc</i> ‘dwelling, specialized farm’, later replaced by Old Norse <i>vithr</i> ‘wood’; initial <i>Sk-</i>, instead of <i>Sh-</i>, is also due to Scandinavian influence."]}]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["variant of   Anne  , in common use as a given name in most European languages. Among people with a classical education, it has from time to time been associated with  Virgil's  Aeneid, where it is borne by the sister of  Dido , Queen of Carthage. This Phoenician name may ultimately be of Semitic origin, and thus related to the biblical <i>Anne</i>. However, the connection, if it exists, is indirect rather than direct."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":37,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":46,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":81,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705190,"age":112,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Anne Skipwith was born in 1178, in England as the daughter of Sir William Skipworth. She married Sir John d'Isney in 1200, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1178–":"1178–Surnud","1178–Female":"1178–Surnud","1185–Male":"1185–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1164–Male":"1164–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1178":"1178","1200":"1200","1164":"1164","about 1200":"umbes 1200","1185":"1185","1290":"1290","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1178–":"1178–Kuollut","1178–Female":"1178–Kuollut","1185–Male":"1185–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1164–Male":"1164–Kuollut","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1178":"1178","1200":"1200","1164":"1164","about 1200":"noin 1200","1185":"1185","1290":"1290","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1178–":"1178–Décédée","1178–Female":"1178–Décédée","1185–Male":"1185–Décédé","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1164–Male":"1164–Décédé","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1178":"1178","1200":"1200","1164":"1164","about 1200":"environ 1200","1185":"1185","1290":"1290","England":"Angleterre","Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Anne Skipwith est née en 1178, à Angleterre, fille de Sir William Skipworth. Elle a épousé Sir John d'Isney en 1200, à Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1178–":"1178–Verstorben","1178–Female":"1178–Verstorben","1185–Male":"1185–Verstorben","1200–Male":"1200–Verstorben","1164–Male":"1164–Verstorben","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1178":"1178","1200":"1